==English==

===Adjective===
'''bathykolpian'''

# [[Deep]] [[bosomed | bosom]]. 
# [[Big]] [[breast | breasted]].
#:'' "The bathykolpian Heré ... sent down Iris" - Oliver Wendell Homes, "Autocrat of the Breakfast-Table" (1858)''

===Etymology===

Derived from greek words ''bathus'' (meaning "deep") and ''kolpos'' (meaning "cleft" or "gulf").

===Pronunciation===

/bath-i-KOL-pee-en/

===Alternate Spellings===

Sometimes spelt "bathukolpian" to more closely represent the greek spelling.